fields.title: Test Post 1
fields.content: We can tell Django which headers will cause the response to vary by decorating the view function with the django.views.decorators.vary.vary_on_headers function.

fields.title: Test Post 3
fields.summary: Used to see 5 most recent posts
fields.content: Try refreshing your browser(s), you should see the log message only on the first request for a user. Subsequent requests don’t execute the view function, and thus won’t output the message. If you want five minutes, or restart the Django dev server (since we’re using local-memory caching) then you should see the message another time.
